      "message": "Same as the GPU commit — there is no NSM Type 2 command to retrieve the number of PCIe functions.\n\nFrom the host side with lspci, the CX8 PCIe switch ports ([15b3:197c]) are all single-function:\n$ lspci -nn | grep \u0027ConnectX\u0027\n15:00.0 PCI bridge: ... ConnectX ... [15b3:197c]   ← .0 only\n16:00.0 PCI bridge: ... ConnectX ... [15b3:197c]   ← .0 only\n16:01.0 PCI bridge: ... ConnectX ... [15b3:197c]   ← .0 only\n...\n\nSince the CX device in dbus-sensors represents the PCIe switch (DEVICE_PCIE), and there is no NSM command to query function count dynamically, we create a single Function0 for the device identity.",
